description:
Solictation

REVOLVER is an original graphic novel by acclaimed writer/artist Matt Kindt (Super Spy, 3 Story: The Secret History of The Giant Man) that's a tale of two worlds - and how both test a man to his limits.  Stuck in a dead-end job with a boss he can't stand and a materialistic girlfriend, Sam rises from a late night of barhopping to discover his whole world has changed.  Literally. 
 
An avian flu outbreak has killed millions, the nation's infrastructure has crashed and a dirty bomb has destroyed Seattle.  Forced to go on the run, Sam awakes to a normal world the next day - and to chaos again the day after that.  A single constant between the two world will undo all the damage, if he can find it - but that seems impossible.  In one world, anything goes.  In the other, he's out of danger and sleepwalking through life.  So Sam's got an even bigger problem:  which world to choose?
name: Revolver

With the help of Martha Jones, the Doctor must reclaim his memory through examining his personal effects, and figure out who has trapped him in this strange prison before it's too late. description: Comic Book Guy: The Comic Book is a five-part comic book mini-series starring the character  Comic Book Guy. The five issues were released between July and November 2010.    In classic Simpsons fashion the books feature many puns and references to film and comic book legends.  For example, the subtitle of book #2 The Death of Comic Book Guy is Funeral for an Acquaintance, a take off on the mourning period following 'The Death of Superman' in the 1992 story arc entitled 'Funeral for a Friend'. (An earlier reference is the Simpsons TV-series episode Funeral for a Fiend featuring Sideshow Bob.)
name: Bongo Comics Presents: Comic Book Guy: The Comic Book

description:
Over a thousand years ago, the great kingdom of China was under constant threat of invasion by powerful tribes and warring states along its rugged western border. For generations, one fiercely-patriotic clan of warriors - the "Yang" - battled bravely in the nation's defense. The widows of the clan pleaded with the Emperor, whose own court had become weakened by corruption and greed, to send reinforcements. But none came. Soon, the last remaining Yang soldiers were overwhelmed by a sea of bloodthirsty invaders. Distraught and incensed, the Yang widows - a few hundred strong and many of whom also seasoned warriors - took arms and set off to the western border. But even before reaching the enemy, the journey itself would be fraught with peril. In their determination to avenge the deaths of their loved ones, the Widow Warriors would face the full fury of nature's most destructive forces, a vast enemy army with sorcery and monsters on its side, and perhaps most powerful of all, the demons within themselves! Pat Lee's return to comics!

Collected in Widow Warriors.
name: Widow Warriors
